 resilient university community News and Updates A one page Emergency Response quick reference guide in now available for download  faculty  staff  and visitors should prepare and respond to emergency situations that may arise while on campus DOWNLOAD HERE  n  nN new  nEmergency Preparedness Classroom Information n  n  npage  nsyllabus  ninsert is now available for all  nfaculty and ninstructors  nThe importance of emergency preparedness extends into the classroom  Faculty  nand instructors who take a few minutes at the start of each  nsemester nto familiarize their students with the  nbasic emergency  nresponse  nprocedures  particular focus on  nactive threat shooter and violent threatening  nsituations n  will find a peace of mind that they and their students are better prepared for an emergency   nNew Emergency Preparedness Classroom Information   page syllabus insert is now available for all faculty and instructors  The importance of emergency preparedness extends into the classroom  Faculty and instructors who take a few minutes at the start of each semester to familiarize their students with the basic emergency response procedures  particular focus on active threat shooter and violent threatening situations  will find a peace of mind that they and their students are better prepared for an emergency DOWNLOAD HERE Emergency Response Guidelines n Emergency Response Guidelines pocket guides are now available  Order yours today  This concise  organized guide outlines instructions on how faculty  staff  and students should prepare for and respond to emergency situations that may arise while on campus  n  n Emergency Whistle Get attention fast  Designed by Search   Rescue professionals chamber design to produce multiple frequency blasts up to     decibels  giving you the best chance of being HEARD and RESCUED in an emergency  Emergency whistles are great in survival situations  natural disaster situations  crime prevention  scaring animals and or any other potential threats  A loud blast from our whistle is an excellent signal for help  easily heard by UIC Police  local law enforcement  campus security and others nearby  Gear up Active Threat Scroll Pen n In high demand  The active threat scroll pen is always on hand to share how best to prepare for  respond to  and recover from this event  At your fingertips  how to build a room barricade  and how to assist your peers during any emergency situation Backpack tags n  Backpack tags go with you everywhere and clip easily on and off student backpacks  Color coded  they instruct where to access emergency updates  inform who to call in a crisis  share medical and emergency contact information Active Threat Wallet Cards n Do you know what to do  Active Threat Wallet Cards show your options and what to do  Get one for your wallet to protect yourself and those around you Products can be picked up at the Paulina St  Building        S  Paulina St  Suite      For more information please contact us at ready uic edu ready uic edu  nALERTS n ALERTS Current status   n NORMAL    nCampus is fully operational at this time Official Campus Announcements   nThere are NO announcements at this time EMERGENCY  CALL     UIC Police Department n               Telecommunications nDevices for the Deaf n               Non Emergency n               Information Hotline n               Facilities Management Services n               Office of Preparedness   Response n                n  n Contact Us Office of Preparedness and Response Office of Preparedness and Response Office of the Vice Chancellor  for Administrative Services Office of the Vice Chancellor  for Administrative Services Web Privacy 